{
  "id": {
    "address": "world",
    "name": "extension_freeze"
  },
  "doc": " Shared types and event for freezing assembly extension configuration.\n Used by Gate, Turret, and StorageUnit so the owner cannot change the extension after freeze (no rugpull).\n\n **Tradeoff:** Once frozen, the assembly cannot be re-authorised to a different or fixed extension package.\n If a bug is found in the extension code, the owner cannot point this assembly at a fixed version; they would\n need to use a new assembly (e.g. anchor a new gate) and authorise the fixed extension there. Freeze only\n after the extension is audited/tested and you are comfortable with this permanence.",
  "immediate_dependencies": [
    {
      "address": "sui",
      "name": "dynamic_field"
    },
    {
      "address": "sui",
      "name": "event"
    },
